        <c02 level="subseries">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Sub-Unit Publications</unittitle>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Sub-Unit Publications include publications from the Center for Sex Equity in Schools. The bibliography <title render="italic">Women, Math and Science: A Resource Manual</title> is a compilation of resources describing the problems and difficulties for young women studying math and science as well as solutions on how to encourage them into these disciplines. The Bentley Library holds the 1984, 1987, and 1996 editions of the manual <title render="italic">Remember the Ladies: A Handbook of Women in American History</title>. The center also published a manual entitled <title render="italic">Susan B. Anthony Day Handbook</title> which gives a short biography of Susan B. Anthony, primary source material relating to Susan B. Anthony, a bibliography of women's issues, and potential classroom activities to celebrate Susan B. Anthony Day. <title render="italic">Women's History Week March 6-12</title> is a series of lesson plans focusing on women in American history.</p>
            <p>The Project for the Fair Administration of Student Discipline includes a bibliography entitled <title render="italic">Student Rights and School Discipline</title> published in 1975. Its update was issued in 1976. This sub-unit also published a report entitled <title render="italic">Assessing Disproportionate Minority Suspensions: A High School Case Study</title> published in 1980.</p>
          </scopecontent>
